Fig. 2

The first entries in the manually compiled database. In the first column, a classification of ten signified a religious occurrence, twenty scientific, thirty political and forty other.

The results, whilst not of first importance in this article, were remarkable, and are illustrated in Fig. 3 . The predominantly religious meaning of âexperimentalâ was overtaken by the new scientific meaning within a decade of the publication of Boyleâs New Experiments in 1660. Although this manual method of analysis took more than 4 weeks, the results and the questions they raised for future research made the effort worthwhile, even though it is now clear that automated methods can achieve similar results in minutes.
